      <hedline>
        <hl1>Following the Leaders</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Claude M Gruener letter on July 25 article on high costs of American automakers of meeting prospective standards to curb global warming; says it would have been nice if American companies had 'done the right thing' and led rather than followed trend of reducing emissions</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Catching Up to the Cost of Global Warming'' (July 25), which reported the high costs to American automakers of meeting prospective standards to curb global warming:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Catching Up to the Cost of Global Warming'' (July 25), which reported the high costs to American automakers of meeting prospective standards to curb global warming:</p>
        <p>One must ask why United States car manufacturers aren't further along in reducing emissions and increasing mileage. As virtually a clear and present danger to the survival of the planet, fuel efficiency in vehicles now has become almost a moral issue. It would have been nice if American companies had ''done the right thing'' and led rather than followed this trend.</p>
        <p>Claude M. Gruener  Austin, Tex., July 25</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
